annotation.TEXT: Looks like Cheese Bridge Area. Umm... I wonder how this game will handle these platforms and saws...
Waaahhh!!! No, Yoshi!!!
Oh, and this seems to be a good place to farm feathers, in case I need to in the future.
Pfft... Hahaha! Well, that sucks! I basically just got Kaizo trapped, because the game acted like I hit the goal even though I was below it, and then I fell to my death instantly!
Wow, that worked better than I expected! And now I'm at midpoint just like that. What a great time-saver!
Okay, can I avoid being Mr. Stupid for a moment here?
Well, at least I can get a reserve feather here.
Demo count: 8
I cleared that one with no problem.
Hmm... Does this game have Yoshi wings?
Nope, it's been swapped out with a feather block.
Hi, Yoshi! Okay, now I'll Start+Select out of here!
At least there doesn't seem to be a super koopa generator here.
Well, I guess that trying for the secret exit here was a total waste of time, but at least it was a hilarious waste of time!
Well, I'm going to reenter and get one cape back at least.
Whoa, and that rope took off without me even touching it. But, it's not like I need it, because I plan to fly here... if I can.
Okay, so what I guess I'll do is play the second half of this level normally first, because backtracking would be tricky with the camera angle the game gives me while moving left.
And I can jump so high that I wouldn't have needed the shell anyway!
Interestingly, spin jumping on a shell-less koopa gives you the same 400 points as stomping it normally does.
Yay! Hey, four out of five is pretty good!
Nope! This one is perfectly safe to exit, thankfully!
And of course, I was right at the goal, too...
Nuts! I could've sworn I was well above that saw! Oh, but using my reserve item immediately lets me continue flying! Awesome!
Oh, yeah, that was REALLY fair, game. (Stupid obvious lack of playtesting...)
Yay!
Ooh, another bonus room! They sure are popping up frequently now. So, what was the deal with them not being where they belonged in some earlier levels?
Yep, that worked, though the pipe doesn't go anywhere. I bet low jumps would've worked in those cases where jumping was not the answer to crossing certain gaps in Lemmy's Castle.
Whoa, that was weird. The victory music got prematurely cutoff there.
Hmm... Can I reach that pipe?
Yay!
Wait, what? I did hit midpoint, right? That Kaizo trap must've nullified my midpoint the instant I "hit" the goal.
So, what will this level be? Find out next time! To be continued...
Thw-thwack. Thwack. Thwack.
Um, what? It looks like Butter Bridge 2, but why did I start at midpoint? I never came here before!
Oh, but could the secret exit possibly be here? Hmm...
Demo count: 9
So, no koopas kicking shells at me here?
D'oh.
Finding a cheap exploit in a cheap game FTW!
Ooh, this pipe goes somewhere! Let's see how well I do this time!
It doesn't appear that cape spins work on blocks, so I'll have to use my head.
Okay, now if I reenter that level, will I start at the beginning?
And, we're back at midpoint, just like that. But, before I leave, I want to do one thing first.
At least I can get my cape right back, but still... That was dumb.
Oh my god. I'm sure it was due to the sprite flickering, but it really looked like Yoshi lost his head when that saw hit him! (There's some nightmare fuel for ya...)
Yes. Now I'm wondering what caused the midpoint to be triggered before I even got here in the first place...

Hello, and welcome back to Lemmy's Castle! Now, I have gone all over this area, even with savestate abuse, and I cannot figure out what this P-switch does at all. There's no hidden door anywhere, and it doesn't summon any vital platforms, so you can just skip it with no problem.
Oh, yeah, and science-- The water does indeed act like a bottomless pit!
Yep, it's there, but whoa, I slipped off! At least I landed safely! (Unlike when I fell into that pit from the sky in Donut Plains 1!)
Oh, man. This part could be tricky...
I bet I can reach that pipe if I do a low jump by holding down as I jump.
Okay, now under the goal we go...
Well, it looks like these line-guided ropes work correctly.
Hi, Yoshi!
Okay, well, I'm ready to move on with the game, so let's see which bridge level the game gives us here...
Got a bit lucky with that gulp.
Or, I could grab onto the rope at a higher point than expected and ride all the way to the end safely!
Science count: 1
Hmm... In the original game, you could fly from around here and find some cloud platforms and coins in the sky. Is that here, too?
Okay, I'm going to do something nutty here and try to fly through the first part. I think I remember where most of the saws were...
What? No cape from stomping that guy? Don't tell me that it's another NES limitation, because you gave me feathers from super koopas just fine in Donut Plains 1.
Oh, come on. I was sure I cleared that.
That was close, and totally not worth it for a worthless coin.
Nuts. Only got one out of five this time. Will I be ambushed as I leave this time?

Oh, and by the way, I had to replay my previous movie to access that level, because as far as I can tell, you can't reenter a crushed castle here, not even with any button combinations I've tried, and the world select feature doesn't fix up the castle either.
Just being cautious. I would've pressed Select while paused there to bail out if it turned out I was going to fall in a pit.
Will this be another bridge level, or Cookie Mountain, or maybe a Vanilla Dome level, somehow? (Vanilla Dome really got the shaft earlier, with half of its levels being from Donut Plains.)
Well, except for the flickering, they seem to be functioning correctly. Also, I bet those saws will actually hurt Yoshi, so let's try to avoid them!
Yay!
Whoa, that was weird. I somehow climbed off the top of the rope and above it briefly.
Not like that.
Yeah, you know what? I'm going to replay that level and try for the secret exit. It'll probably be very tricky, but I want to try anyway.
